## Project Overview

This project is a Bash automation script designed for system administrators and DevOps teams to rapidly triage and categorize system log entries (`app_output.log`) into actionable assignments.

It uses a chain of standard Linux text processing tools (`grep` and `sed`) to filter relevant log messages and substitute severity keywords with assigned owner IDs (e.g., `ERROR ‚Üí ERROR-mccoy`, `INFO ‚Üí INFO-spock`).

This project demonstrates practical log analysis, pattern matching, and bulk text transformation in a professional Linux environment.

---

## üîë Key Features

- **Targeted Triage:** Filters only relevant log entries using `grep`
- **Role Assignment:** Substitutes severity keywords with owner IDs
- **Case Insensitive:** Handles `info`, `Info`, `INFO`, etc.
- **Non-Destructive:** Preserves the original log file
- **Fast Execution:** Processes large log files in seconds

